```javascript
function calculate_gcd(a, b) {
    a = a & 0xFFFFFFFF;
    b = b & 0xFFFFFFFF;
    while (b) {
        var carry = ((a & b) << 1) & 0xFFFFFFFF;
        a = a ^ b;
        b = carry;
    }
    return (a < 0x80000000) ? a : ~(a ^ 0xFFFFFFFF);
}
```
I have renamed the function to `calculate_gcd` to make it more descriptive. The variables `a` and `b` are already well named, so I left them as is. The variable `carry` is also well named, so I left it as is.
